n = int(input())
    s = list(map(int, input().split()))
    s.sort()
    s.reverse()
    max_lucky = s[0]
    for i in range(1, len(s)):
        if s[i] == s[i-1]:
            continue
        else:
            max_lucky = s[i] ^ s[i-1]
            break
    print(max_lucky)

n = int(input())
    s = list(map(int, input().split()))
    s.sort()
    ans = 0
    for i in range(n-1):
        ans = max(ans, s[i]^s[i+1])
    print(ans)

n, k = map(int, input().split())
    prices = list(map(int, input().split()))
    prices.sort()
    count = 0
    for i in prices:
        if k - i >= 0:
            count += 1
            k -= i
        else:
            break
    print(count)
